SIMPLE: eared
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eared
<hw>Eared</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having (such
or so many) ears; -- used in composition; <as>as,
long-<ex>eared-eared</ex>; sharp-<ex>eared</ex>; full-<ex>eared</ex>;
ten-<ex>eared</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>Having external ears; having
tufts of feathers resembling ears.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Eared owl</b></col> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>, <cd>an owl
having earlike tufts of feathers, as the <stype>long-eared owl</stype>,
and <stype>short-eared owl</stype>.</cd> -- <col><b>Eared seal</b></col>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>, <cd>any seal of the family
<fam>Otariid⟦ae⟧</fam>, including the fur seals and hair seals. See
<er>Seal</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>earflap</ent>⟦br⟧
